This chart shows the neighborhood corridors with the highest average rideshare fares. Corridors are created by pairing pickup and drop-off neighborhoods, removing intra-neighborhood travel. To avoid outliers, corridors with very low trip counts (≤20) are filtered out. The data is then ranked by taking weighted average of the trip cost, and the top 20 most expensive corridors are displayed.

The chart highlights which commonly traveled routes have the highest rideshare costs, often reflecting longer distances, high-demand routes, or areas with limited alternative transportation options.